But tensorflow does support complex number, right?
I can even create variable type as this:<tf.Tensor 'Exp:0' shape=() dtype=complex128>
sess.run(y3)
(1.8369701987210297e-16+3j)

I guess my question now is since tensorflow does support complex number, why does it output NaN?
Some operations in tf does support, and some does not? If possible I wish this issue to still be open, so people can work on the operations that does not support complex numbers.
